To find the last digit of the entire sum, we need to compute the sum of the last digits of \( k^2 \) for \( k \) from 1 to 2401 modulo 10. The last digits of squares modulo 10 repeat every 10 numbers with the sequence [1, 4, 9, 6, 5, 6, 9, 4, 1, 0]. The sum of these last digits for one block of 10 numbers is \( 1 + 4 + 9 + 6 + 5 + 6 + 9 + 4 + 1 + 0 = 45 \), which is congruent to 5 modulo 10.
